description:
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield Health is Britain’s largest not-for-profit healthcare organisation. Join us as a Porter in our Tunbridge Wells Hospital and play your part in building a healthier nation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this varied and physical role as a Hospital Porter you will;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collect and return patients to their individual rooms following surgery.&lt;br /&gt;Work alongside trained professionals ensuring that the theatre environment and equipment is fully functioning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support the cleaning of theatre equipment and environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be working in a fast moving clinical environment, with constant interaction with the Theatre Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Person&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To succeed as a Porter you will;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be comfortable with a physical role which involves pushing beds and lifting heavy equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be a good communicator as part of your role will be ensuring that patients are feeling as relaxed and reassured prior to their surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comply with Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) checks if successful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Benefits&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Holiday in line with the Working Time Directive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to our Pension Scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discounted gym membership at £15.00 a month that they need to set up directly with the club. Discount does not extend to partners and family members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working on the bank means you are not contracted to a set number of hours per week but instead work on an ad-hoc basis to suit the needs of the business and your availability. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key information about the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary - £8.70 Per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location - Tunbridge Wells&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contract Type - Bank&lt;br /&gt;Weekly Hours - Various Hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date - 04/12/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post.&lt;/p&gt;
